# Cursor Rules - React Vite App

## Quick Reference
- **Architecture**: Bulletproof React pattern (see AGENTS.md)
- **Docs**: See `docs/` folder for detailed guides

## Key Rules

### File Naming
- Use kebab-case: `my-component.tsx`, `use-my-hook.ts`
- Pages use default exports for lazy loading

### Imports
- Always use `@/` alias, never relative paths across directories
- Import from barrel exports: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/features/auth`
- Never import from internal paths like `@/components/ui/button/button`

### Where to Put Code
- UI primitives → `src/components/ui/[name]/`
- Layouts → `src/components/layouts/`
- Feature code → `src/features/[name]/`
- Shared hooks → `src/hooks/`
- Pages → `src/pages/` (kebab-case, default export)

### Component Structure
```
src/components/ui/[name]/
├── [name].tsx    # Component
└── index.ts      # Export { ComponentName } from "./[name]"
```

### Feature Structure
```
src/features/[name]/
├── components/   # Feature components
├── hooks/        # Feature hooks
├── lib/          # Feature utilities
├── types/        # Feature types
└── index.ts      # Public API only
```

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utilities
- Use `cn()` from `@/utils` for conditional classes
- Define variants as const objects

### Testing
- Co-locate tests: `__tests__/[name].test.tsx`
- Use custom render from `@/testing`

## Don't
- Don't import between features directly
- Don't put business logic in UI components
- Don't skip barrel exports
- Don't use PascalCase for filenames
